            <thetext>The qooxdoo-API-documentation says that the property &quot;height&quot; of the qx.client.NativeWindow specifies the outer height of the window. But if I set this property by
myWin.setHeight(400);
the outer height will be 400px plus possible scrollbar, titlebar, statusbar. So the method setHeight() sets the inner height and not as described in the documentation the outer height. The same applies to the &quot;width&quot;.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
